SIMPLE: transfiguratien
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transfiguratien
<hw>Trans*fig`u*ra"tien</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transfiguratio</ets>: cf. <ets>transfiguration</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A change of form or appearance; especially, the
supernatural change in the personal appearance of our Savior on the
mount.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A feast held by some branches of
the Christian church on the 6th of August, in commemoration of the
miraculous change above mentioned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transfigure</ent>⟦br⟧
